name: Cycling
description: Cycling, also, when on a two-wheeled bicycle, called bicycling or biking, is the use of cycles for transport, recreation, exercise or sport.

name: Swimming
description: Swimming is the self-propulsion of a person through water, or other liquid, usually for recreation, sport, exercise, or survival.

name: Walking
description: Walking is one of the main gaits of terrestrial locomotion among legged animals. Walking is typically slower than running and other gaits.

name: Squats
description: A squat is a strength exercise in which the trainee lowers their hips from a standing position and then stands back up.

name: Running
description: Running is a method of terrestrial locomotion allowing humans and other animals to move rapidly on foot.
